<item>
            <title>[LU-7227] Add a check to t-f that dmesg doesn&apos;t have critical messages</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7227</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;For example, conf-sanity 62 causes error message:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;VFS: Busy inodes after unmount of loop0. Self-destruct in 5 seconds. Have a nice day... &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Similar message could be seen after each test. So we need extra check in test cleanup.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There were several issues with missed iput - for example &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5729&quot; title=&quot;VFS: Busy inodes after unmount of loop0. Self-destruct in 5 seconds. Have a nice day...&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-5729&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-5729&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Provided patch will help to find similar problems in future.&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;Busy inodes&quot; is just one of error messages that tells about internal kernel problems. &lt;br/&gt;
I hope list of error messages in check_dmesg_for_errors will be supplemented by developers.  &lt;/p&gt;</description>
